00:19:59.510 --> 00:20:02.090
that you have on today's
generation of teenagers.

00:20:08.040 --> 00:20:10.090
AUDIENCE: So I know
that online bullying

00:20:10.090 --> 00:20:14.340
is a uniquely bad problem
for this generation,

00:20:14.340 --> 00:20:17.840
and I was curious what
your social network is

00:20:17.840 --> 00:20:20.105
doing to mitigate that problem.

00:20:20.105 --> 00:20:20.730
CORY LEVY: Yes.

00:20:20.730 --> 00:20:24.190
So online bullying is a
very, very serious problem

00:20:24.190 --> 00:20:27.410
for pretty much any
big social network.

00:20:27.410 --> 00:20:31.070
One of the things that we
do is proactive moderation.

00:20:31.070 --> 00:20:34.100
So most social networks
do reactive moderation.

00:20:34.100 --> 00:20:38.690
When someone posts a message
to Twitter or Facebook,

00:20:38.690 --> 00:20:40.220
it gets seen by everyone.

00:20:40.220 --> 00:20:42.290
If it is a negative
message, it may

00:20:42.290 --> 00:20:44.610
get taken down after the fact.

00:20:44.610 --> 00:20:46.900
With After School, we
do product moderation.

00:20:46.900 --> 00:20:48.890
So when someone
writes a message,

00:20:48.890 --> 00:20:51.350
it has to get seen by
moderation in order for it

00:20:51.350 --> 00:20:53.270
to get seen by others.

00:20:53.270 --> 00:20:58.370
So that's one of the steps
that we take in After School,

00:20:58.370 --> 00:21:00.950
and we hope that other social
networks will follow and just

00:21:00.950 --> 00:21:06.020
increase moderation and yeah.

